[[!meta title="Energy Drink — Gorilla Mind Red Gummy Fish"]]
[[!tag Energy_Drink Review]]

Ghost Energy, about a year ago, discontinued its Swedish Fish flavor along with
its [[Sour Patch Kids Redberry|Ghost_Energy_x_Sour_Patch_Kids_Redberry]] and
[[Sour Patch Kids Blue Raspberry|Ghost_Energy_x_Sour_Patch_Kids_Blue_Raspberry]]
flavors when it stopped collaboration with Mondelez, the maker of both Sour
Patch Kids and Swedish Fish in the US. I liked Ghost's Swedish Fish flavor a lot
and was dissappointed to see it go.

Gorilla Mind has picked up the slack in the market. Last December it began
offering the "Red Gummy Fish" flavor I picked up today. I know _exactly_ what
those are supposed to be.

Unsurprisingly, this is another [[Exxon]] pull.

<figure>
[[!template id="hooya-img.tmpl" cid="bafkreigwh5c3wpi2xszrlfeiysxyb3oigrgxny245zpwkumzhoqqd6ifky" size=medium]]
</figure>

The combination of extreme carbonation and a heavy-handed dose of citric acid
creates an extremely sour drink. Unsurprisingly the profile reminds me of a
Ghost. After the sour punch evaporates I'm left with a waxy taste on my tongue.
They really nailed the <s>Swedish Fish</s> Red Gummy Fish flavor.

| | Amount |
| --- | --- |
| Volume | 16 floz |
| Calories | 15cal |
| Caffeine | 200mg |

